A. Core Languages used in Windows
  1. C (foundation layer)
    a. The Windows kernel and low-level components are largely written in C
    b. C is used because it provides 
      a. Direct memory access
      b. Fine-grained hardware control
      c. High Performance
  2. C++ (major system components)
    a. large part of Windows are written in C++
    b. Used for:
      a. System libraries
      b. File systems
      c. UI frameworks
      d. core services
  3. Assembly language (hardware-level code)
    a. used in very small but critical sections 
      a. boot loaders 
      b. context switching
      c. cpu-specific routines
  4. C# (higher-level features)
    a. used in more modern parts of Windows 
      a. some system tools
      b. UI components
      c. Applications and services
    b. closely tied to the .NET framework
* Takeaway how it fits together
  + Hardware Layer - assembly
  + Kernel Layer - C
  + System Layer - C++ 
  + Application/UI layer - C# (and others)
